11:04.992 --> 11:07.158
Wait, hold on, Ted
What are we doing?

11:07.160 --> 11:08.576
You're arguing
about Robin's wealth

11:08.578 --> 11:11.046
when you really should be asking
me embarrassing questions.

11:11.048 --> 11:12.597
He's right.

11:12.599 --> 11:13.515
Let's do this.

11:13.517 --> 11:14.966
NARRATOR:
<i>And so we did it.</i>

11:14.968 --> 11:16.668
<i>We asked Barney</i>
<i>all the questions</i>

11:16.670 --> 11:17.652
<i>we'd always wanted to.</i>

11:17.654 --> 11:20.355
In one night? Four.

11:20.357 --> 11:22.991
In one family? Three.

11:22.993 --> 11:26.361
Yes, but not while she
was secretary of state.

11:26.363 --> 11:29.981
Yes, but not while <i>she</i> was
secretary of state.

11:29.983 --> 11:31.399
Just once.

11:31.401 --> 11:34.435
With a French male model Henri.

11:34.437 --> 11:35.704
It was late.

11:35.706 --> 11:37.622
We were the last two people
in the club.

11:37.624 --> 11:40.075
I was lonely and I figured,
why not try it?

11:41.377 --> 11:44.145
That was the only time
I ever split a cab.

11:44.147 --> 11:46.998
Yes, but not the M.I.T.
you're thinking of.

11:47.000 --> 11:49.884
The Magician's Institute
of Teaneck.

11:49.886 --> 11:53.588
I've had sex
in Ted's bed 14 times.

11:53.590 --> 11:57.125
I asked if you wear
shoulder pads.

11:57.127 --> 11:59.644
I think I've just got
one question left.

11:59.646 --> 12:01.212
And it's a biggie.

12:02.064 --> 12:04.315
Barney Stinson...

12:04.317 --> 12:06.568
...what do you do for a living?

12:09.388 --> 12:10.505
You did it.

12:10.507 --> 12:13.307
You banged your wife to sleep.

12:13.309 --> 12:15.493
Nice job...

12:17.279 --> 12:19.831
Still-Big Fudge.

12:22.484 --> 12:24.619
TED:
I wuv you, Mommy.

12:24.621 --> 12:25.787
Unpause.

12:29.613 --> 12:31.606
NARRATOR: <i>Kids, in all the time</i>
<i>we knew Barney,</i>

12:31.607 --> 12:34.658
<i>there was one question he would</i>
<i>always answer the same way.</i>

12:34.660 --> 12:36.393
Seriously, what is it
that you do?

12:36.395 --> 12:37.778
(chuckles) Please.

12:37.780 --> 12:38.745
Okay, seriously.

12:38.747 --> 12:40.414
What do you do for a living?

12:40.416 --> 12:42.049
(chuckles) Please.

12:42.051 --> 12:44.284
Are you finally gonna tell me
exactly what your job is?

12:44.286 --> 12:45.953
(chuckles) Please.

12:45.955 --> 12:48.772
<i>So, naturally, this was</i>
<i>a pretty big moment for us.</i>

12:48.774 --> 12:52.742
Well, what do you do
for a living?

12:56.247 --> 12:58.081
Please.

12:58.083 --> 12:59.349
(groans)
God, he's not telling us.

12:59.351 --> 13:00.350
More booze.

13:00.352 --> 13:02.803
Not so fast, princess.

13:02.805 --> 13:04.638
I guess subtle clues
and the bar tab

13:04.640 --> 13:06.607
are two things
you just don't pick up.

13:06.609 --> 13:07.757
Because...

13:07.759 --> 13:10.227
I think he is telling us.

13:10.229 --> 13:12.529
Tell us more about this job.

13:13.448 --> 13:14.681
BARNEY:
<i>Well, as you know,</i>

13:14.683 --> 13:16.283
<i>back in my hippie days,</i>

13:16.285 --> 13:18.235
<i>a business man came</i>
<i>into my coffee shop,</i>

13:18.237 --> 13:20.070
<i>told me money was</i>
<i>all that mattered,</i>

13:20.072 --> 13:21.488
<i>and stole my girlfriend.</i>

13:21.490 --> 13:25.108
<i>That's when I decided</i>
<i>to become awesome.</i>

13:25.110 --> 13:28.645
<i>But I had no idea how to break</i>
<i>into the corporate world.</i>

13:28.647 --> 13:30.047
<i>So, hoping he wouldn't</i>
<i>recognize me,</i>

13:30.049 --> 13:31.781
<i>I went to the one person</i>
<i>from whom</i>

13:31.783 --> 13:34.384
<i>I knew I could learn</i>
<i>everything.</i>

13:34.386 --> 13:35.802
Do we know each other, bro?

13:35.804 --> 13:39.473
We're all connected
in Gaia's great tapestry of...

13:39.475 --> 13:41.558
(clears throat)
No.

13:41.560 --> 13:42.893
We don't.

13:42.895 --> 13:44.728
Bro.

13:46.014 --> 13:47.347
Wow, you went to M.I.T.

13:47.349 --> 13:48.515
Pretty impressive.

13:48.517 --> 13:51.401
I did get a perfect score
on the A.C.T.'s.

13:51.403 --> 13:54.404
Advanced Card Tricks.

13:54.406 --> 13:55.606
Well, look, buddy.

13:55.608 --> 13:57.107
You got a sweet résumé.

13:57.109 --> 13:59.192
But we don't have any openings
you're qualified for.

13:59.194 --> 14:01.862
They set me up!
It was a trap! It's a trap!

14:03.814 --> 14:06.466
We have one opening
you'd be perfect for.

14:06.468 --> 14:08.535
Great. What do I do?

14:08.537 --> 14:10.621
Please.

14:10.623 --> 14:13.040
"Provide Legal Exculpation
And Sign Everything."

14:13.042 --> 14:14.257
Just show up every day,

14:14.259 --> 14:15.976
scribble your name on
a bunch of documents,

14:15.978 --> 14:18.011
and we'll pay you
16 craploads a year.

14:19.163 --> 14:20.297
Deets are in the contract.

14:20.299 --> 14:21.739
I'll give you time
to think about it.

14:23.301 --> 14:24.718
I'll take it.

14:24.720 --> 14:25.769
Hold on.

14:25.771 --> 14:27.421
Did you even read this
before signing it?

14:27.423 --> 14:28.388
No.

14:28.390 --> 14:29.723
(laughs)
You're hired.

14:32.310 --> 14:33.276
We'll work on that.

14:33.278 --> 14:34.645
TED:
<i>Wait.</i>

14:34.647 --> 14:35.646
That's your job?

14:35.648 --> 14:37.864
You sign sketchy,
legally binding documents

14:37.866 --> 14:40.017
that could implicate you
for God knows what?

14:40.019 --> 14:42.169
Best job ever, right?

14:43.388 --> 14:45.455
No more pausing.

14:45.457 --> 14:47.157
We're getting
through this argument.

14:47.159 --> 14:49.042
Okay.

14:49.044 --> 14:51.011
No potshots at my mom.

14:51.013 --> 14:52.796
Fine, no distracting me
with your calves.

14:52.798 --> 14:54.998
Fine.

14:58.603 --> 15:01.054
Look, I love you, Lilypad.

15:01.056 --> 15:02.723
I love you, Marshmallow.

15:02.725 --> 15:04.641
(deep breath)
Now...

15:04.643 --> 15:06.309
(exhales)

15:06.311 --> 15:09.613
...how could you take
that job without telling me?!

15:09.615 --> 15:12.564
Baby, I'm sorry, but they needed
an answer right away.

15:12.565 --> 15:13.681
This is a huge opportunity,

15:13.683 --> 15:15.400
it could be very good
for our family,

15:15.402 --> 15:17.352
and we have to
at least talk about it.

15:17.354 --> 15:20.104
Sorry, you lost your chance
to talk about it

15:20.106 --> 15:22.156
when you didn't talk about it.

15:22.891 --> 15:24.475
We're going to Italy.

15:24.477 --> 15:25.943
But I could be a judge.

15:25.945 --> 15:29.080
We can't give that up for
what is clearly just a hobby.

15:29.082 --> 15:30.248
Pause.

15:30.250 --> 15:31.499
No pause.

15:31.501 --> 15:33.484
That "hobby" is my dream.

15:33.486 --> 15:35.169
We're going to Italy.

15:35.171 --> 15:36.254
But it's my dream to...

15:36.256 --> 15:37.505
We are going to Italy!

15:37.507 --> 15:38.873
Baby, can you just...?

15:38.875 --> 15:40.508
We are going to Italy!

15:40.510 --> 15:41.709
Don't you get it?

15:41.711 --> 15:43.878
You went behind my back.

15:43.880 --> 15:45.596
You hurt me.

15:45.598 --> 15:49.567
You were more selfish
than I have ever been to you.

15:49.569 --> 15:54.472
You broke up with me
and moved to San Francisco.

15:55.607 --> 15:57.392
Barney!
You're being stupid.

15:57.394 --> 15:59.894
The-the-the company is
setting you up as their fall guy

15:59.896 --> 16:02.480
for all of their
illegal activities.

16:02.482 --> 16:05.316
No, you guys are being stupid.

16:05.318 --> 16:06.868
Especially Ted.

16:06.870 --> 16:08.453
What? I didn't say anything.

16:08.455 --> 16:12.240
NARRATOR: <i>And then, kids, Barney revealed</i>
<i>to us his master plan.</i>

16:12.242 --> 16:14.776
<i>It all went down a few months</i>
<i>after the wedding.</i>

16:14.778 --> 16:16.694
Hey, Greg?

16:16.696 --> 16:18.046
I know you're busy,

16:18.048 --> 16:20.114
but FYI, I've been colluding
with the Feds.

16:20.116 --> 16:21.382
They know everything.

16:21.384 --> 16:22.917
And they're
on their way up right now

16:22.919 --> 16:24.552
to shut down this division
and arrest you.

16:24.554 --> 16:25.887
Door closed or...?

16:25.889 --> 16:27.221
What?

16:27.223 --> 16:28.589
Why would you do that?

16:28.591 --> 16:31.225
Oh, gosh,
countless moral reasons...

16:31.227 --> 16:32.643
could have applied,

16:32.645 --> 16:36.431
but this is pretty much revenge
for stealing my girlfriend.

16:36.433 --> 16:38.048
<i>See? That day, I vowed</i>

16:38.050 --> 16:40.551
<i>I would do everything</i>
<i>in my power to track you down,</i>

16:40.553 --> 16:42.270
<i>gain your trust,</i>

16:42.272 --> 16:45.022
<i>and then destroy you.</i>

16:45.024 --> 16:46.324
Who are you?

16:46.326 --> 16:47.358
Who am I?

16:47.360 --> 16:49.026
Just a guy who served you

16:49.028 --> 16:50.561
coffee once.

16:50.563 --> 16:51.846
Peace out, loser.

16:51.848 --> 16:53.698
♪ Barney Stinson,
Barney Stinson ♪

16:53.700 --> 16:55.333
You son of a bitch!
♪ That guy's awesome ♪

16:55.335 --> 16:58.068
I will destroy you!
Get your hands off of me.

16:58.070 --> 17:01.189
♪ Oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh

17:01.191 --> 17:03.541
♪ Awesome.

17:03.543 --> 17:05.009
Why are you

17:05.011 --> 17:06.594
bringing up San Francisco?

17:06.596 --> 17:08.628
That was seven years ago.

17:08.631 --> 17:10.580
Because you are being

17:10.583 --> 17:12.967
selfish all over again.

17:12.969 --> 17:14.852
Marshall, I apologized

17:14.854 --> 17:17.421
over and over again.

17:17.423 --> 17:20.141
Now you're saying you
never have forgiven me?

17:20.143 --> 17:21.275
There is

17:21.277 --> 17:24.194
nothing more important to me
than our family.

17:24.196 --> 17:25.445
You know that.

17:25.448 --> 17:26.696
Well, let me ask.

17:26.699 --> 17:29.233
What if you had found
success in San Francisco?

17:29.968 --> 17:31.452
How do I know that you even

17:31.454 --> 17:32.670
would've come back to me?

17:32.672 --> 17:34.438
Stop it.

17:34.440 --> 17:35.907
Are Marvin and I

17:35.909 --> 17:38.543
and any other future children
we may have

17:38.545 --> 17:41.129
just some consolation prize?

17:41.131 --> 17:43.297
I have to get out of here.

17:45.617 --> 17:46.584
Babe?

17:46.586 --> 17:48.886
(door slams)

17:48.888 --> 17:50.087
So, Barney,

17:50.089 --> 17:51.589
I still haven't
heard you pronounce

17:51.591 --> 17:53.007
that last syllable.

17:53.809 --> 17:57.228
At our wedding, will there be

17:57.230 --> 17:59.680
a ring bear-er?

17:59.682 --> 18:01.182
(deep breath)

18:01.184 --> 18:02.934
The truth is...

18:03.836 --> 18:06.838
...yes, there will be
a ring bear-er.

18:06.840 --> 18:08.823
His name is Trevor Hudson,

18:08.825 --> 18:10.958
I worked with his mother,
and he's adorable.

18:10.960 --> 18:13.778
I want our wedding
to be perfect, Robin.

18:13.780 --> 18:15.613
Me, too.

18:16.582 --> 18:17.648
Okay, I'm gonna go upstairs.

18:17.650 --> 18:18.783
He's okay to crash
with you, right?

18:18.785 --> 18:20.868
Yup, we'll see you
in the morning.

18:20.870 --> 18:22.537
Hmm.

18:22.539 --> 18:23.704
I love you.

18:23.706 --> 18:25.506
I love you, too.

18:29.428 --> 18:32.296
Okay, I got one last question
for you.

18:32.298 --> 18:34.398
And I can't believe
I haven't asked it yet.

18:34.400 --> 18:37.034
Dude, you're getting
married tomorrow.

18:38.203 --> 18:40.171
How are you doing?
Good.

18:40.173 --> 18:42.773
I mean, I'm a little nervous,

18:42.775 --> 18:46.510
but I love Robin more
than I've ever loved anyone,

18:46.512 --> 18:49.130
and I'm gonna do everything
I can to make her happy.

18:49.132 --> 18:50.648
For a long time,

18:50.650 --> 18:52.850
deep down,

18:52.852 --> 18:55.019
I've felt sort of...

18:55.021 --> 18:57.788
broken?

18:57.790 --> 19:00.241
I don't feel that way anymore.

19:00.243 --> 19:02.526
Robin, along with the idea

19:02.528 --> 19:05.296
that vengeance
will soon be mine,

19:05.298 --> 19:09.133
has made me 100% awesome.

19:09.135 --> 19:10.401
I'm proud of you, buddy.

19:10.403 --> 19:13.387
Globan froban.

19:13.389 --> 19:14.472
Ho, ho, ho.

19:14.474 --> 19:15.473
Okay.

19:15.475 --> 19:16.724
Come on, Jabba.

19:16.726 --> 19:17.675
Big day tomorrow.

19:17.677 --> 19:19.844
(grunts)
Tab for the night?

19:19.846 --> 19:21.378
Just so you know,

19:21.380 --> 19:24.899
those last few rounds of 35-year
Glen McKenna were not cheap.

19:24.901 --> 19:25.983
Whoa.

19:25.985 --> 19:27.051
Um...

19:27.053 --> 19:28.402
you know what?

19:28.404 --> 19:29.687
Charge them to the bride's room.

19:29.689 --> 19:30.855
Thank you.

19:30.857 --> 19:31.889
Come on.
(muttering)

19:31.891 --> 19:33.824
Let's go. We got you.

19:33.826 --> 19:36.577
NARRATOR: <i>Kids, it's your</i>
<i>grandmother's favorite rule.</i>

19:36.579 --> 19:38.930
<i>Nothing good happens</i>
<i>after 2:00 a.m.</i>

19:38.932 --> 19:42.066
Hi. I-I know it's late,
but I've got to get out of here.

19:42.068 --> 19:45.086
Marshall and I
just had a huge fight.

19:45.088 --> 19:47.371
You will?

19:47.373 --> 19:50.124
Oh, my God, thank you.

